        "created_at": "2018-05-03T02:23:04.176Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Ok thanks. So, imagine a client which is written against version 500 of the API. I want a way for that client to be able to run unmodified throughout cluster upgrades, and without needing to manually provision new library files to the instance. If all clients need to be manually reprovisioned with new binaries every time the cluster is upgraded it removes most of the benefit of having a multiversion API.</p>\n<p>So I propose we lock down the initial version header in the network API. I want a client to be able to connect, wait for the server to say \u201cFDB 5.1.7\u201d, then disconnect, fetch the appropriate <code>fdb_c</code> library file from <a href=\"http://foundationdb.org\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">foundationdb.org</a> and connect and run as normal.</p>",
